---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Na Hua Kukui was founded to perpetuate the ancient principles and healing practice of Lomi Lomi in the line of Kahu Abraham Kawaii."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Na Hua Kukui",
      "url": "https://nahuakukui.com/about",
      "description": "Perpetuating the ancient principles and healing practice of Lomi Lomi in the line of Kahu Abraham Kawaii."
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  {/* Page Hero */}
  <section class="bg-bg-dark pt-32 pb-20 md:pt-40 md:pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-gold mb-6">About</h1>
      <p class="text-text-inverse/70 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Na Hua Kukui was founded to perpetuate the ancient principles and healing practice of Lomi Lomi (Massage) in the line of Kahu Abraham Kawaii.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Bio Section A: Kahu Abraham Kawaii */}
  <section class="bg-bg-light py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-accent/10 rounded-sm overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center">
          <img
            src="/images/kahu-abraham.jpg"
            alt="Kahu Abraham Kawaii"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-accent mb-4">
            Kahu Abraham Kawaii
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted uppercase tracking-wide mb-6">The Source</p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Kahu Abraham was a native Hawaiian from Honaunau, Hawaii, who was skilled in numerous traditional healing practices. After years of training with Kupuna, Kahuna and Olohe within his immediate and extended family he decided to share his knowledge of Kahuna Principles with the wider world.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            He believed the wealth of knowledge inherent in Hawaiian Culture could be valuable to all. In Kahu's words: <em class="text-accent">&ldquo;It is not a matter of blood but a matter of spirit.&rdquo;</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Kahu founded Na Pua Olohe (The Flowers of Wisdom) in 1989, as a way to bring his teachings to the public. In the years following, Kahu held workshops and lectures, offered consultations and private sessions from his home on Kauai and around the world.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed">
            By applying natural principles his teachings develop character, dignity and deep perceptive abilities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Bio Section B: Jody Mountain */}
  <section class="bg-bg-light py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-accent/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-accent mb-4">
            Jody Mountain
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted uppercase tracking-wide mb-6">Teacher</p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Jody Mountain is a direct student of Kahu Abraham Kawai&rsquo;i, Aua&rsquo;ia, Maka&rsquo;i&rsquo;ole, &lsquo;Uliama, and brings forward the teaching of this lineage. Since 1989, she has been studying, practicing and teaching the art of Ancient Lomi Lomi and its foundations in Ancient Hawaiian Wisdom.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            She has an extensive background in movement modalities such as dance, choreography, and healing embodiment practices. Jody also practices and facilitates Core &amp; Cellular Healing &mdash; a modern form of Ancient Hawaiian Ho&rsquo;oponopono.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed">
            She is a licensed Massage Therapist and Teacher in the state of Hawai&rsquo;i, and has dedicated her life to sharing the depth and vibrancy of this profound work with others as a vehicle for awakened consciousness.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 md:order-2 aspect-[3/4] bg-accent/10 rounded-sm overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center">
          <img
            src="/images/jody-mountain.jpg"
            alt="Jody Mountain"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Bio Section C: Zen Kekoa Powers */}
  <section class="bg-bg-light py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-accent/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="aspect-[3/4] bg-accent/10 rounded-sm overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center">
          <img
            src="/images/kekoa-powers.jpg"
            alt="Zen Kekoa Powers"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-accent mb-4">
            Zen Kekoa Powers
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted uppercase tracking-wide mb-6">Practitioner</p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Kekoa is a married father of two, a permaculture practitioner, Licensed Massage Therapist and accredited teacher of Ho&rsquo;omanamana. Born in a thatched hut of bamboo and coconut fronds in East M&#257;ui, Kekoa was raised in rural farming communities in Hawaii, Kansas and the Colorado Rockies.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Growing up in close relationship to the natural world, he has developed an acute awareness of the relationship between the environment and one&rsquo;s internal ecosystem. Kekoa has been studying and practicing Lomi Ke Ala H&#333;k&#363; since 2013 and became accredited to teach Ho&rsquo;omanamana in 2020.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text/80 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Ho&rsquo;omanamana is one of the foundational movement practices within this lineage that opens pathways of innate perception in the body. Within this ancient paradigm of healing one may reconnect with the part of themselves capable of holding a wider spectrum of being and in so doing reunite with the essential aspect of life which recognizes kinship with all things.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get in touch</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Closing */}
  <section class="bg-bg-dark py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="font-serif text-lg md:text-xl text-text-inverse/70 italic leading-relaxed">
        The kukui oil burned in the hands of those who came before. What passes through these sessions is the same light, carried forward.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
